    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted under a risk-informed rationale: model influence is Medium, decision consequence is Medium, and bench testing across two independent laboratories with N=11 specimens provides sufficient confidence in FEA predictions. All three primary QoIs satisfy E/uval < 1.96 and <10% difference acceptance criteria. Overall credibility is sufficient to support the intended regulatory use.",
